        <!-- ========== USAGE ========== -->
        <div class="tab-content" id="tab-usage" style="display:none;padding-top:32px;">
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="when-to-use" class="doc-section-title">When and Where to Use</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Progress bars communicate measurable completion status across uploads, processing, and system operations.</p>
            <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:24px;margin-top:24px;">
              <div style="padding:24px;background:var(--prism-surface);border:1px solid var(--prism-border);border-radius:12px;">
                <h3 style="font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:var(--prism-text);margin-bottom:16px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;"><svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="#2563eb" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>When to use</h3>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="border:none;background:transparent;padding-left:20px;font-size:14.5px;">
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;">To show <strong>measurable progress</strong> toward a known completion point (file upload, form completion, steps completed).</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;">To communicate <strong>system status</strong> during a background operation (syncing, processing, building).</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;">When the user benefits from knowing <strong>how much remains</strong>, not just that something is happening.</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;">Use <strong>Indeterminate</strong> when the duration or percentage cannot be calculated.</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;">Use <strong>Success / Warning / Error</strong> variants when the completion state carries a semantic outcome.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div style="padding:24px;background:var(--prism-surface);border:1px solid var(--prism-border);border-radius:12px;">
                <h3 style="font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:var(--prism-text);margin-bottom:16px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;"><svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="#e42527" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg>When NOT to use</h3>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="border:none;background:transparent;padding-left:20px;font-size:14.5px;">
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;"><strong>Step-by-step workflows</strong> &#8212; use a Wizard instead. Progress bars don't communicate discrete steps clearly.</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;"><strong>Circular loading</strong> &#8212; use Progress Loader for spinners inside buttons or inline loaders.</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;"><strong>Binary complete / incomplete</strong> &#8212; use a Checkbox or a simple status indicator.</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;"><strong>Page-level loading</strong> &#8212; use a top-of-page slim bar (e.g. NProgress pattern), not a full-width labelled progress bar.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <hr class="doc-divider"/>
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="indeterminate-mode" class="doc-section-title">Indeterminate Mode</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">When the total duration or steps of an operation are unknown, use variant="Indeterminate". The fill stub is a fixed-width segment (~33% of the track) that sweeps from left to right in a continuous animation.</p>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li><strong>Value label:</strong> Render "&#8212;" (em dash) or omit it entirely. Do not show "0%" &#8212; that implies 0% is known, which contradicts the indeterminate state.</li>
              <li><strong>Animation:</strong> Apply <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">overflow: hidden</code> on the Track element so the fill clips at the track boundaries.</li>
              <li><strong>Reduced motion:</strong> Respect <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">prefers-reduced-motion</code> &#8212; pause the animation and show a static 33% fill.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <hr class="doc-divider"/>
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="detailed-guidelines" class="doc-section-title">Complete Do's and Don'ts</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Guidelines for effective progress bar usage.</p>
            <div class="do-dont-grid">
              <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span><ul>
                <li><strong>Use Large for prominent page-level progress;</strong> Small for dense lists or tables.</li>
                <li><strong>Keep the label concise</strong> (2&#8211;4 words: "Upload progress", "Storage used").</li>
                <li><strong>Show the % value</strong> alongside the bar so users can read the exact number.</li>
                <li><strong>Use Indeterminate</strong> when duration cannot be computed.</li>
                <li><strong>Transition to Success</strong> variant at 100% completion.</li>
                <li><strong>Set width: 100%</strong> in code so the bar fills its container.</li>
                <li><strong>Animate fill width</strong> with transition: width 300ms ease.</li>
                <li><strong>Respect prefers-reduced-motion</strong> &#8212; use instant updates instead of animations.</li>
              </ul></div>
              <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span><ul>
                <li><strong>Use Large inside a compact list item.</strong></li>
                <li><strong>Write a full sentence</strong> as the label.</li>
                <li><strong>Rely on bar width alone</strong> for precision &#8212; perception is inaccurate.</li>
                <li><strong>Show 0% or a frozen bar</strong> while waiting &#8212; it implies the operation is stuck.</li>
                <li><strong>Leave the bar in Default</strong> state after completion.</li>
                <li><strong>Reset to 0% on error</strong> without feedback.</li>
                <li><strong>Use Warning</strong> for purely in-progress states.</li>
                <li><strong>Hard-code the 280 px</strong> canvas width.</li>
                <li><strong>Force animations</strong> regardless of user preference.</li>
              </ul></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <hr class="doc-divider"/>
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="related" class="doc-section-title">Related</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Components that complement or can be used alongside the Progress Bar.</p>
            <div class="related-grid">
              <a href="Progress-indicator.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 6v6l4 2"/></svg> Progress Loader</a>
              <a href="Slider.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="4" y1="12" x2="20" y2="12"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/></svg> Slider</a>
              <a href="Tabs.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M4 6h16M4 12h16M4 18h8"/></svg> Tabs</a>
              <a href="Snackbar.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="3" y="5" width="18" height="14" rx="3"/></svg> Toast / Snackbar</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <hr class="doc-divider"/>
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="references" class="doc-section-title">References</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Design tokens and resources for implementing the Progress Bar component.</p>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li><strong>Figma Node:</strong> <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">17012:973360</code> &#8212; Component Set: Progress Bar</li>
              <li><strong>Total Variants:</strong> 4 determinate variants &times; 2 states &times; 5 fill levels &times; 3 sizes + 1 indeterminate &times; 2 states &times; 3 sizes = <strong>126 variants</strong></li>
              <li><strong>Typography:</strong> Zoho Puvi Medium (500) for all sizes</li>
              <li><strong>Border Radius:</strong> <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">9999px</code> (fully rounded pill)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- ========== CODE ========== -->
        <div class="tab-content" id="tab-code" style="display:none;padding-top:32px;">
          <h2 id="live-demo-code" class="doc-section-title">Live demo (Code)</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Configure the Progress Bar component and view generated HTML.</p>
          <div class="code-playground">
            <div class="cp-toolbar">
              <div class="cp-control-group"><label class="cp-label">Variant</label><select class="cp-select" id="pg-variant"><option value="default">Default</option><option value="success">Success</option><option value="warning">Warning</option><option value="error">Error</option><option value="indeterminate">Indeterminate</option></select></div>
              <div class="cp-control-group"><label class="cp-label">Size</label><select class="cp-select" id="pg-size"><option value="sm">Small</option><option value="md" selected>Medium</option><option value="lg">Large</option></select></div>
              <div class="cp-control-group"><label class="cp-label">Value (%)</label><input class="cp-select" id="pg-value" type="number" min="0" max="100" value="25" style="width:100%;"></div>
              <div class="cp-control-group"><label class="cp-label">Label</label><input class="cp-select" id="pg-label" type="text" value="Uploading" style="width:100%;"></div>
              <div class="cp-control-group"><label class="cp-label">Show Label</label><select class="cp-select" id="pg-showlabel"><option value="true" selected>Yes</option><option value="false">No</option></select></div>
              <div class="cp-control-group"><label class="cp-label">Disabled</label><select class="cp-select" id="pg-disabled"><option value="false" selected>No</option><option value="true">Yes</option></select></div>
            </div>
            <div class="cp-preview" id="pg-preview-area">
              <div id="pg-bar-el" class="pb pb-default pb-md" style="width:320px;" role="progressbar" aria-valuenow="25" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100">
                <div class="pb-label-row"><span class="pb-label">Uploading</span><span class="pb-value">25%</span></div>
                <div class="pb-track"><div class="pb-fill" style="width:25%;"></div></div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="cp-code-header">
              <div style="font-size:13.5px;font-weight:600;color:var(--prism-text);">HTML</div>
              <button class="cp-action-btn" id="pg-copy-btn"><svg width="15" height="15" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M8 7v8a2 2 0 002 2h6M8 7V5a2 2 0 012-2h4.586a1 1 0 01.707.293l4.414 4.414a1 1 0 01.293.707V15a2 2 0 01-2 2h-2M8 7H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h8a2 2 0 002-2v-2"/></svg> Copy code</button>
            </div>
            <div class="cp-code-area" id="pg-code-output"></div>
          </div>
          <script>
          (function(){
            var els = {variant:document.getElementById('pg-variant'),size:document.getElementById('pg-size'),value:document.getElementById('pg-value'),label:document.getElementById('pg-label'),showlabel:document.getElementById('pg-showlabel'),disabled:document.getElementById('pg-disabled')};
            var barEl = document.getElementById('pg-bar-el');
            var codeOut = document.getElementById('pg-code-output');
            var copyBtn = document.getElementById('pg-copy-btn');
            function esc(s){return s.replace(/&/g,'&amp;').replace(/</g,'&lt;').replace(/>/g,'&gt;').replace(/"/g,'&quot;');}
            function update(){
              var v=els.variant.value, sz=els.size.value, val=parseInt(els.value.value)||0, lbl=els.label.value||'Progress', showLbl=els.showlabel.value==='true', dis=els.disabled.value==='true';
              if(val<0) val=0; if(val>100) val=100;
              var isIndet = v==='indeterminate';
              var cls='pb pb-'+v+' pb-'+sz;
              if(dis) cls+=' pb-disabled';
              barEl.className=cls;
              barEl.style.width='320px';
              // Label row
              var labelRow=barEl.querySelector('.pb-label-row');
              var labelSpan=barEl.querySelector('.pb-label');
              var valueSpan=barEl.querySelector('.pb-value');
              var fill=barEl.querySelector('.pb-fill');
              if(showLbl){
                labelRow.style.display='flex';
                labelSpan.textContent=lbl;
                valueSpan.textContent=isIndet?'\u2014':val+'%';
              } else {
                labelRow.style.display='none';
              }
              if(!isIndet){
                fill.style.width=val+'%';
                barEl.setAttribute('aria-valuenow',val);
              } else {
                fill.style.width='';
                barEl.removeAttribute('aria-valuenow');
              }
              barEl.setAttribute('role','progressbar');
              barEl.setAttribute('aria-valuemin','0');
              barEl.setAttribute('aria-valuemax','100');
              if(dis) barEl.setAttribute('aria-disabled','true'); else barEl.removeAttribute('aria-disabled');
              barEl.setAttribute('aria-label',lbl);
              // Code output
              var ariaAttrs=' role="progressbar" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"';
              if(!isIndet) ariaAttrs+=' aria-valuenow="'+val+'"';
              ariaAttrs+=' aria-label="'+lbl+'"';
              if(dis) ariaAttrs+=' aria-disabled="true"';
              var valText=isIndet?'\u2014':val+'%';
              var fillW=isIndet?'':' style="width:'+val+'%;"';
              var code='<div class="'+cls+'"'+ariaAttrs+'>\n';
              if(showLbl) code+='  <div class="pb-label-row">\n    <span class="pb-label">'+lbl+'</span>\n    <span class="pb-value">'+valText+'</span>\n  </div>\n';
              code+='  <div class="pb-track">\n    <div class="pb-fill"'+fillW+'></div>\n  </div>\n</div>';
              codeOut.innerHTML=esc(code).replace(/class=&quot;(.*?)&quot;/g,'<span style="color:#38bdf8;">class</span>=<span style="color:#34d399;">"$1"</span>').replace(/role=&quot;(.*?)&quot;/g,'<span style="color:#38bdf8;">role</span>=<span style="color:#34d399;">"$1"</span>').replace(/aria-\w+=&quot;(.*?)&quot;/g,function(m){return m.replace(/^(aria-\w+)=&quot;(.*?)&quot;$/,function(_,a,b){return '<span style="color:#38bdf8;">'+a+'</span>=<span style="color:#34d399;">"'+b+'"</span>';});}).replace(/style=&quot;(.*?)&quot;/g,'<span style="color:#38bdf8;">style</span>=<span style="color:#34d399;">"$1"</span>').replace(/&lt;(\/?)(div|span)(.*?)&gt;/g,'&lt;$1<span style="color:#a78bfa;">$2</span>$3&gt;');
            }
            Object.values(els).forEach(function(e){e.addEventListener(e.tagName==='INPUT'?'input':'change',update);});
            copyBtn.addEventListener('click',function(){
              var r=document.createElement('div');r.innerHTML=codeOut.innerHTML;
              navigator.clipboard.writeText(r.innerText).then(function(){
                var o=copyBtn.innerHTML;copyBtn.innerHTML='<svg width="15" height="15" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg> Copied!';setTimeout(function(){copyBtn.innerHTML=o;},2000);
              });
            });
            update();
          })();
          </script>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="component-api-properties" class="doc-h3">Component API &amp; Properties</h3>
            <table class="size-table">
              <thead><tr><th>Property</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td><code>variant</code></td><td>'Default' | 'Success' | 'Warning' | 'Error' | 'Indeterminate'</td><td>'Default'</td><td>Semantic colour and mode. Use Indeterminate when duration is unknown.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>size</code></td><td>'Small' | 'Medium' | 'Large'</td><td>'Small'</td><td>Controls track height and typography scale.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>value</code></td><td>number</td><td>25</td><td>Current progress value (0&#8211;100). Ignored when variant='Indeterminate'.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>max</code></td><td>number</td><td>100</td><td>Maximum value. Used to compute fill percentage: (value / max) * 100.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>label</code></td><td>string</td><td>"Progress"</td><td>Left-side descriptive label text.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>showLabel</code></td><td>boolean</td><td>true</td><td>Shows or hides the entire label row (both label and percentage text).</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>valueLabel</code></td><td>string</td><td>"25%"</td><td>Right-side value display string. Defaults to "&#8212;" when variant='Indeterminate'. Override to show custom strings (e.g. "3 of 12 tasks").</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>disabled</code></td><td>boolean</td><td>false</td><td>Applies the disabled visual state.</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
          <hr class="doc-divider"/>
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="code-examples" class="doc-h3">Code Examples</h3>
            <h4 style="font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--prism-text);margin-bottom:16px;">Default &#8212; 25% progress</h4>
            <div class="cp-code-area" style="border-radius:12px;margin-bottom:24px;">
              <div style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:13.5px;line-height:1.6;">
                <span style="color:#ABB2BF;">&lt;</span><span style="color:#E06C75;">ProgressBar</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">label</span><span style="color:#56B6C2;">=</span><span style="color:#98C379;">"Uploading"</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">value</span><span style="color:#56B6C2;">=</span><span style="color:#C678DD;">{25}</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">max</span><span style="color:#56B6C2;">=</span><span style="color:#C678DD;">{100}</span><br>
                <span style="color:#ABB2BF;">/&gt;</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <h4 style="font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--prism-text);margin-bottom:16px;">Success at 100%</h4>
            <div class="cp-code-area" style="border-radius:12px;margin-bottom:24px;">
              <div style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:13.5px;line-height:1.6;">
                <span style="color:#ABB2BF;">&lt;</span><span style="color:#E06C75;">ProgressBar</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">variant</span><span style="color:#56B6C2;">=</span><span style="color:#98C379;">"Success"</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">label</span><span style="color:#56B6C2;">=</span><span style="color:#98C379;">"Analysis complete"</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">value</span><span style="color:#56B6C2;">=</span><span style="color:#C678DD;">{100}</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">max</span><span style="color:#56B6C2;">=</span><span style="color:#C678DD;">{100}</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">valueLabel</span><span style="color:#56B6C2;">=</span><span style="color:#98C379;">"Done"</span><br>
                <span style="color:#ABB2BF;">/&gt;</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <h4 style="font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--prism-text);margin-bottom:16px;">Warning &#8212; storage near capacity</h4>
            <div class="cp-code-area" style="border-radius:12px;margin-bottom:24px;">
              <div style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:13.5px;line-height:1.6;">
                <span style="color:#ABB2BF;">&lt;</span><span style="color:#E06C75;">ProgressBar</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">variant</span><span style="color:#56B6C2;">=</span><span style="color:#98C379;">"Warning"</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">label</span><span style="color:#56B6C2;">=</span><span style="color:#98C379;">"Storage used"</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">value</span><span style="color:#56B6C2;">=</span><span style="color:#C678DD;">{82}</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">max</span><span style="color:#56B6C2;">=</span><span style="color:#C678DD;">{100}</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">size</span><span style="color:#56B6C2;">=</span><span style="color:#98C379;">"Medium"</span><br>
                <span style="color:#ABB2BF;">/&gt;</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <h4 style="font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--prism-text);margin-bottom:16px;">Indeterminate &#8212; unknown duration</h4>
            <div class="cp-code-area" style="border-radius:12px;margin-bottom:24px;">
              <div style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:13.5px;line-height:1.6;">
                <span style="color:#ABB2BF;">&lt;</span><span style="color:#E06C75;">ProgressBar</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">variant</span><span style="color:#56B6C2;">=</span><span style="color:#98C379;">"Indeterminate"</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">label</span><span style="color:#56B6C2;">=</span><span style="color:#98C379;">"Processing&#8230;"</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">size</span><span style="color:#56B6C2;">=</span><span style="color:#98C379;">"Medium"</span><br>
                <span style="color:#ABB2BF;">/&gt;</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <h4 style="font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--prism-text);margin-bottom:16px;">Without label row (track only)</h4>
            <div class="cp-code-area" style="border-radius:12px;margin-bottom:24px;">
              <div style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:13.5px;line-height:1.6;">
                <span style="color:#ABB2BF;">&lt;</span><span style="color:#E06C75;">ProgressBar</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">value</span><span style="color:#56B6C2;">=</span><span style="color:#C678DD;">{60}</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">showLabel</span><span style="color:#56B6C2;">=</span><span style="color:#C678DD;">{false}</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">size</span><span style="color:#56B6C2;">=</span><span style="color:#98C379;">"Small"</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">aria-label</span><span style="color:#56B6C2;">=</span><span style="color:#98C379;">"Profile completion"</span><br>
                <span style="color:#ABB2BF;">/&gt;</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <h4 style="font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--prism-text);margin-bottom:16px;">Custom value label &#8212; steps</h4>
            <div class="cp-code-area" style="border-radius:12px;margin-bottom:24px;">
              <div style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:13.5px;line-height:1.6;">
                <span style="color:#ABB2BF;">&lt;</span><span style="color:#E06C75;">ProgressBar</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">label</span><span style="color:#56B6C2;">=</span><span style="color:#98C379;">"Onboarding"</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">value</span><span style="color:#56B6C2;">=</span><span style="color:#C678DD;">{3}</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">max</span><span style="color:#56B6C2;">=</span><span style="color:#C678DD;">{8}</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">valueLabel</span><span style="color:#56B6C2;">=</span><span style="color:#98C379;">"Step 3 of 8"</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">size</span><span style="color:#56B6C2;">=</span><span style="color:#98C379;">"Large"</span><br>
                <span style="color:#ABB2BF;">/&gt;</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <h4 style="font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--prism-text);margin-bottom:16px;">Responsive fill (CSS)</h4>
            <div class="cp-code-area" style="border-radius:12px;margin-bottom:24px;">
              <div style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:13.5px;line-height:1.6;">
                <span style="color:#94a3b8;">/* Responsive fill */</span><br>
                <span style="color:#E06C75;">.progress-bar</span> {<br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">width</span>: <span style="color:#C678DD;">100%</span>;<br>
                }<br>
                <span style="color:#E06C75;">.progress-bar__fill</span> {<br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">width</span>: <span style="color:#C678DD;">calc(var(--progress-value, 0) * 1%)</span>;<br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">transition</span>: <span style="color:#C678DD;">width 300ms ease</span>;<br>
                }<br><br>
                <span style="color:#C678DD;">@media</span> (<span style="color:#D19A66;">prefers-reduced-motion: reduce</span>) {<br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#E06C75;">.progress-bar__fill</span> { <span style="color:#D19A66;">transition</span>: <span style="color:#C678DD;">none</span>; }<br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#E06C75;">.progress-bar--indeterminate .progress-bar__fill</span> {<br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">animation</span>: <span style="color:#C678DD;">none</span>;<br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#D19A66;">width</span>: <span style="color:#C678DD;">33%</span>;<br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;}<br>
                }
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <hr class="doc-divider"/>
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="rtl-support" class="doc-h3">RTL Support</h3>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li>No RTL axis exists in the Figma component. Implement RTL by mirroring the fill direction in CSS: <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">direction: rtl</code> or <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">transform: scaleX(-1)</code> on the track.</li>
              <li>The label row should also reverse: percentage left-aligned, label right-aligned in RTL contexts.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- ========== ACCESSIBILITY ========== -->
        <div class="tab-content" id="tab-accessibility" style="display:none;padding-top:32px;">
          <h2 id="accessibility" class="doc-section-title">Accessibility</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Guidelines for ensuring progress bar elements are accessible across assistive technologies.</p>
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="aria-attributes-screen-reader-guidance" class="doc-h3">ARIA Attributes &amp; Screen Reader Guidance</h3>
            <table class="size-table">
              <thead><tr><th>Concern</th><th>Requirement</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td><strong>Role</strong></td><td>Use <code>role="progressbar"</code> on the track element.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Value attributes</strong></td><td>Set <code>aria-valuenow</code>, <code>aria-valuemin="0"</code>, <code>aria-valuemax="100"</code> dynamically.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Indeterminate</strong></td><td>Omit <code>aria-valuenow</code> when variant="Indeterminate" &#8212; its absence signals the value is unknown.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Label</strong></td><td>Provide <code>aria-label</code> or <code>aria-labelledby</code> referencing the label text. e.g. <code>aria-label="File upload progress"</code>.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Value text</strong></td><td>Use <code>aria-valuetext</code> when the visual label is non-numeric (e.g. "Step 3 of 8").</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Disabled state</strong></td><td>Set <code>aria-disabled="true"</code> on the container; visually greyed tokens already applied.</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
          <hr class="doc-divider"/>
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="live-region-announcements" class="doc-h3">Live Region Announcements</h3>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li><strong>aria-live="polite":</strong> Wrap in <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-live="polite"</code> to announce progress changes to screen readers.</li>
              <li><strong>Throttle announcements:</strong> Avoid flooding the screen reader by throttling updates (e.g. announce every 10% or at key milestones).</li>
              <li><strong>Completion:</strong> Announce completion explicitly (e.g. "Upload complete") when reaching 100%.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <hr class="doc-divider"/>
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="keyboard-interaction" class="doc-h3">Keyboard Interaction</h3>
            <div style="margin-top:16px;padding:16px 20px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.05);border:1px solid rgba(37,99,235,0.15);border-radius:12px;">
              <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--prism-text);line-height:1.6;margin:0;">Progress bars are read-only, non-interactive elements. They do not receive keyboard focus. The surrounding context (form, dialog, or page) conveys the progress information.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <hr class="doc-divider"/>
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="color-contrast-minimums" class="doc-h3">Color Contrast Minimums<span class="h3-badge" style="background:rgba(34,197,94,0.15);color:#16a34a;">WCAG AA Pass</span></h3>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Fill colour on track background must be distinguishable. All four Solid fill tokens meet sufficient contrast against their Secondary track tokens in UEMS Light theme.</p>
            <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(280px,1fr));gap:20px;margin-top:24px;">
              <div style="background:var(--prism-surface);border:1px solid var(--prism-border);border-radius:12px;overflow:hidden;">
                <div style="background:#D5E0F8;padding:28px 24px;text-align:center;"><div style="width:60%;height:8px;border-radius:9999px;background:#2C66DD;margin:0 auto;"></div></div>
                <div style="padding:16px 24px;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;border-top:1px solid var(--prism-border);"><div><div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--prism-text-muted);font-weight:600;">DEFAULT</div><div style="font-size:15px;color:var(--prism-text);font-family:monospace;margin-top:4px;">#2C66DD on #D5E0F8</div></div><div style="text-align:right;"><div style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;background:rgba(34,197,94,0.1);color:#16a34a;padding:4px 10px;border-radius:100px;font-size:12px;font-weight:700;"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg> Pass</div><div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--prism-text-muted);margin-top:4px;font-weight:600;">WCAG AA</div></div></div>
              </div>
              <div style="background:var(--prism-surface);border:1px solid var(--prism-border);border-radius:12px;overflow:hidden;">
                <div style="background:#E7F3ED;padding:28px 24px;text-align:center;"><div style="width:100%;height:8px;border-radius:9999px;background:#0C8844;margin:0 auto;"></div></div>
                <div style="padding:16px 24px;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;border-top:1px solid var(--prism-border);"><div><div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--prism-text-muted);font-weight:600;">SUCCESS</div><div style="font-size:15px;color:var(--prism-text);font-family:monospace;margin-top:4px;">#0C8844 on #E7F3ED</div></div><div style="text-align:right;"><div style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;background:rgba(34,197,94,0.1);color:#16a34a;padding:4px 10px;border-radius:100px;font-size:12px;font-weight:700;"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg> Pass</div><div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--prism-text-muted);margin-top:4px;font-weight:600;">WCAG AA</div></div></div>
              </div>
              <div style="background:var(--prism-surface);border:1px solid var(--prism-border);border-radius:12px;overflow:hidden;">
                <div style="background:#FEF8EB;padding:28px 24px;text-align:center;"><div style="width:80%;height:8px;border-radius:9999px;background:#E6930A;margin:0 auto;"></div></div>
                <div style="padding:16px 24px;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;border-top:1px solid var(--prism-border);"><div><div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--prism-text-muted);font-weight:600;">WARNING</div><div style="font-size:15px;color:var(--prism-text);font-family:monospace;margin-top:4px;">#E6930A on #FEF8EB</div></div><div style="text-align:right;"><div style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;background:rgba(34,197,94,0.1);color:#16a34a;padding:4px 10px;border-radius:100px;font-size:12px;font-weight:700;"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg> Pass</div><div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--prism-text-muted);margin-top:4px;font-weight:600;">WCAG AA</div></div></div>
              </div>
              <div style="background:var(--prism-surface);border:1px solid var(--prism-border);border-radius:12px;overflow:hidden;">
                <div style="background:#FDEBEB;padding:28px 24px;text-align:center;"><div style="width:43%;height:8px;border-radius:9999px;background:#E42527;margin:0 auto;"></div></div>
                <div style="padding:16px 24px;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;border-top:1px solid var(--prism-border);"><div><div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--prism-text-muted);font-weight:600;">ERROR</div><div style="font-size:15px;color:var(--prism-text);font-family:monospace;margin-top:4px;">#E42527 on #FDEBEB</div></div><div style="text-align:right;"><div style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;background:rgba(34,197,94,0.1);color:#16a34a;padding:4px 10px;border-radius:100px;font-size:12px;font-weight:700;"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg> Pass</div><div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--prism-text-muted);margin-top:4px;font-weight:600;">WCAG AA</div></div></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <hr class="doc-divider"/>
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="motion-sensitivity" class="doc-h3">Motion Sensitivity</h3>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Indeterminate animation must pause when prefers-reduced-motion: reduce is set.</p>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li><strong>Reduced motion:</strong> When <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">prefers-reduced-motion: reduce</code> is active, disable the sweep animation and show a static 33% fill stub.</li>
              <li><strong>Determinate transitions:</strong> Also disable <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">transition: width 300ms ease</code> so the fill updates instantly.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <hr class="doc-divider"/>
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h3 id="rtl-accessibility" class="doc-h3">RTL Considerations</h3>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li>No RTL axis exists in the Figma component. Implement RTL by mirroring the fill direction in CSS: <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">direction: rtl</code> or <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">transform: scaleX(-1)</code> on the track.</li>
              <li>Ensure <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-valuenow</code> and other ARIA attributes remain unchanged &#8212; screen readers handle directionality natively.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        </div><!-- main-content-inner -->

